Cek Null¶

In [11]:
def cek_null(df):
    col_na = df.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    percent = col_na / len(df)
    missing_data = pd.concat([col_na, percent], axis=1, keys=['Total', 'Percent'])
    print(missing_data[missing_data['Total'] > 0])
In [12]:
for idx, data in enumerate(data_year):
    print("Penanganan data untuk dekade", year[idx])
    cek_null(data)
    # Isi data null dengan mode nya
    data['genre'].fillna(data['genre'].mode()[0],inplace = True)
    print("==== Setelah Diisi ====")
    cek_null(data)
    print("\n")

In [17]:
arr = ['title','artist', 'genre', 'has_win_award', 'year']

for c in data_all_year.columns:
    if c not in arr:
        data = data_all_year[c]
        Q1_column = data.quantile(0.25)
        Q3_column = data.quantile(0.75)
        IQR_column = Q3_column - Q1_column
        mask = data_all_year.loc[(data < (Q1_column - 1.5 * IQR_column)) | (data > (Q3_column + 1.5 * IQR_column))]
        #if c == 'acous':
        #    data_all_year = data_all_year.drop(data_all_year[(data_all_year[c] < (Q1_column - 1.5 * IQR_column)) | (data_all_year[c] > (Q3_column + 1.5 * IQR_column))].index)
        #else:
        data_all_year.loc[mask.index, c] = data.mean(skipna=True)
            
    else:
        continue

for idx, data in enumerate(data_year):
    sum_popularity = data.groupby(by=["artist"]).sum()
    sum_popularity.sort_values(by='popularity', inplace=True, ascending=False)
    first = sum_popularity.iloc[0]
    print("Artis paling populer dari dataset", year[idx], "adalah", first.name, "dengan total nilai popularitas sebesar", first.popularity)

In [28]:
from sklearn.metrics import precision_score, \
    recall_score, classification_report, \
    accuracy_score, f1_score, ConfusionMatrixDisplay

def performance(actual, predicted):
    print("Hasil Evaluasi:\n\n%s\n" % (classification_report(actual, predicted)))
    print('Accuracy:', accuracy_score(actual, predicted))
    print('Precision Macro Average:', precision_score(actual, predicted, average='macro'))
    print('Precision Micro Average:', precision_score(actual, predicted, average='micro'))
    print('Recall Macro Average:', recall_score(actual, predicted, average='macro'))
    print('Recall Micro Average:', recall_score(actual, predicted, average='micro'))
    print('F1 Macro Average:', f1_score(actual, predicted, average='macro'))
    print('F1 Micro Average:', f1_score(actual, predicted, average='micro'))

Similarity TSNE pada feature ke 5==x1 (live) dan feature 4==x2 (dB) pada data_copy
Sehingga bila reduction dilakukan dengan TSNE, dapat ditarik kesimpulan bahwa semakin keras suara suatu lagu maka maka lagu tersebut lebih mungkin bukan merupakan live recording dan berlaku sebaliknya.
Hal ini cukup masuk akal karena kebanyakan lagu live recording volume suaranya tidak keras karena tidak ada enhancement atau tuning (overdubbing) dan direkam secara normal dalam studio musik.

Dari kedua proyeksi diatas, dimensionality reduction menggunakan T-SNE lebih menghasilkan cluster yang bagus jika digunakan algoritma clustering nantinya ketimbang dengan menggunakan PCA

Dengan T-SNE, hasil clustering lebih solid karena preserve small distance ketimbang PCA yang hasil clusteringnya tersebar karena maximizing variance

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans, AgglomerativeClustering
# K-means dan Agglomerative dengan library sklearn

kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=2)
agg = AgglomerativeClustering(n_clusters=2, affinity='euclidean', linkage='single')
df_tsne['cluster_k'] = kmeans.fit_predict(df_tsne)
df_tsne['cluster_a'] = agg.fit_predict(df_tsne)

# Add colors and clustering
df_tsne['c_k'] = df_tsne.cluster_k.map({0:colors[0], 
                                        1:colors[1]})
df_tsne['c_a'] = df_tsne.cluster_a.map({0:colors[0], 
                                        1:colors[1]})

In [67]:
alpha_max = 0
r2_highest = 0
for alpha in [ 0.0001, 0.01,0.1, 0.15, 0.16, 0.2, 0.5, 1, 2, 5, 10]:
  ls = Lasso(alpha=alpha, max_iter = 10000)
  ls.fit(x_train, y_train)
  y_pred_ls = ls.predict(x_test)
  r2_ls = metrics.r2_score(y_test,y_pred_ls)
  if r2_ls > r2_highest:
    r2_highest = r2_ls
    alpha_max = alpha


print("R-Squared for alpha", alpha_max, ":", r2_highest)

from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV

gradient_regresson = GradientBoostingRegressor(
    loss="absolute_error",
    n_estimators = 1000,
    criterion="friedman_mse",
    max_depth=10
)

param_grid = {'loss': ["absolute_error"],
              'n_estimators': [100,200,300],
              'criterion': ["squared_error"],
              }
 
grid = GridSearchCV(gradient_regresson, param_grid, refit = True, verbose = 3)

grid.fit(x_train, y_train)
y_pred_gradient = grid.predict(x_test)

# print best parameter after tuning
print("\nBest Param : {}".format(grid.best_params_))
# print how our model looks after hyper-parameter tuning
print("\nBest estimator : {}".format(grid.best_estimator_))

print("Results of sklearn.metrics:")
print("MAE:",metrics.mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred_gradient))
print("MSE:", metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_gradient))
print("RMSE:", np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred_gradient)))
print("R-Squared:", metrics.r2_score(y_test, y_pred_gradient))
